Practical 02 :- Design a student registration form using various HTML form elements. 
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html> 
 
<head> 
    <title>Student Registration Form</title> 
</head> 
 
<body> 
 
    <h1 style="text-align:center;">Student Registration Form</h1> 
 
    <form style = "width: 400px; margin:auto;"> 
 
        <label>Full Name:</label><br> 
        <input type="text" name="fullname" style="width:100%; "> 
        <br><br> 
 
        <label>Email Address:</label><br> 
        <input type="email" name="email" style="width:100%;"> 
        <br><br> 
 
        <label>Password:</label><br> 
        <input type="password" name="password" style="width:100%; "> 
        <br><br> 
 
        <label>Gender:</label><br> 
        <input type="radio" name="gender"> Male 
        <input type="radio" name="gender"> Female 
        <input type="radio" name="gender"> Other 
        <br><br> 
 
        <label>Date of Birth:</label><br> 
        <input type="date" name="dob" style="width:100%; "> 
        <br><br> 
 
        <label>Select Course:</label><br> 
        <select style="width:100%; "> 
            <option>BCA</option> 
            <option>BSc</option> 
            <option>BBA</option> 
            <option>MCA</option> 
        </select> 
        <br><br> 
 
        <label>Hobbies:</label><br> 
        <input type="checkbox"> Reading 
        <input type="checkbox"> Sports 
        <input type="checkbox"> Music 
        <input type="checkbox"> Traveling 
        <br><br> 
 
        <label>Address:</label><br> 
        <textarea rows="4" cols="30" style="width:100%; "></textarea> 
        <br><br> 
 
        <label>Phone Number:</label><br> 
        <input type="tel" name="phone" style="width:100%; "> 
        <br><br> 
 
        <input type="submit" value="Register"> 
    </form> 
</body> 
</html> 
